THE Minister for Culture, Arts and Sports Mohamed Mchengerwa has commended Simba for their Sunday night 1-0 victory over Orlando Pirates. Mchengerwa made the remarks on behalf of the government after the country’s envoys displayed a stellar performance against the South Africa’s football giants. Minister Mchengerwa led thousands of Tanzanian football fans to cheer Simba at the Benjamin Mkapa Stadium and helped the team to emerge victorious. Simba who fought bravely against tactical South Africans eventually won at the end to brings the club close to tournament’s semis. It was defender Shomari Kapombe who brought joy to the passionate Simba fans after scoring the worthy goal for his team. Orlando Pirates fought hard to level the score, but none of their efforts paid off until the end of the tense 90 minutes. It was a slim, but a very crucial win for the Tanzanian envoys as they just need a draw in a return leg to sail to the tournament’s semis. At the full packed Benjamin Mkapa stadium, Simba fans added colours to the victory as they wholeheartedly supported their team and their support paid off handsomely. Simba converted the spot-kick into the 68th minute through Shomari Kapombe. Pirates fought hard to level the score in the last twenty minutes, but Simba's solid defence led by Mohammed Hussein, Henoc Inonga and Pascal Wawa kept Simba safe. 